# Hume EVI Next.js Starter Project Overview

## Project Purpose
This is a **Hume Empathic Voice Interface (EVI)** starter template built with Next.js 14.2.3. The project provides a foundation for building voice-enabled applications with emotional intelligence capabilities using Hume AI's SDK.

**CRITICAL**: We are ADDING functionality to this existing project, NOT rebuilding from scratch. Every line of code should enhance the existing application.

## Core Technologies
- **Framework**: Next.js 14.2.3 with App Router pattern
- **Voice AI**: Hume AI Voice SDK (`@humeai/voice-react` v0.1.15)
- **UI Framework**: Tailwind CSS with Radix UI components
- **Animation**: Framer Motion for smooth transitions
- **Language**: TypeScript
- **Package Manager**: pnpm

## Key Files
- **Entry Point**: [app/page.tsx](mdc:app/page.tsx) - Main application page
- **Layout**: [app/layout.tsx](mdc:app/layout.tsx) - Root layout with metadata
- **Global Styles**: [app/globals.css](mdc:app/globals.css) - Tailwind and custom styles
- **Package Config**: [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Dependencies and scripts
- **TypeScript Config**: [tsconfig.json](mdc:tsconfig.json) - TypeScript settings
- **Tailwind Config**: [tailwind.config.ts](mdc:tailwind.config.ts) - Tailwind customization
- **Components Config**: [components.json](mdc:components.json) - UI components configuration

## Development Commands
```bash
pnpm dev     # Start development server on http://localhost:3000
pnpm build   # Build for production
pnpm start   # Start production server
pnpm lint    # Run ESLint
```

## Project Structure Pattern
The project follows Next.js 14 App Router conventions:
- `/app` - Application routes and pages
- `/components` - Reusable React components
- `/utils` - Utility functions and helpers
- `/public` - Static assets
